{
  "doc_id": "56514",
  "text": "When a number of strains compete for a single resource, namely susceptible individuals, in the most general case the only outcome of the competition is competitive exclusion. Under this scenario, one strain persists, while the others are eliminated. The strain that outcompetes and eliminates the rest is the one that can persist on the lowest number of susceptibles, that is, the strain with the largest reproduction number [CITATION_1] .",
